    <label>Derelict Casino</label>
	<scenario>
		<summary>A hungover casino owner wakes up in his forgotten dusty paradise.</summary>
		<description>There was a time where your casino was bustling, people betting large quantities of silver over petty games. At some point the guests stopped coming. The machines started malfunctioning, and cobwebs forming on the bar counter. Each day became a struggle just to keep the lights on, and a struggle to keep your relationship with alcohol in check. Last night, your loneliness got the best of you. You chugged the last bit of alcohol you had in your storeroom, just to feel something again.

You wake up outside in the old parking lot with a bruise on your head, and a pulsating headache. Perhaps last night was the wakeup call you needed.</description>
